      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "REIKO JETSON (1) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by a neck at Launceston in a handy 30.18 beating Impulsive Miss. Winner at his latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Looks the testing material. SNOWFALL (8) is rarely out of the finish, recording seven places from 12 starts. Has finished in the placings two on end now, the latest when second (30.06) at Launceston. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Bold showing expected. DON'T TELL TOMMY (4) produced an impressive win last time in quickest of the meeting when scoring by 5.5 lengths (19.07) at this track. Harder here but expected to feature again. TRICK (2) was out of the money at this circuit last start but can atone.",
